CREATE TABLE tickets (ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, category VARCHAR(50), status VARCHAR(20), created_at TIMESTAMP, closed_at TIMESTAMP, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id)) ENGINE=InnoDB

CREATE TABLE interactions (interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY, ticket_id INT, message TEXT, interaction_type VARCHAR(20), interaction_time TIMESTAMP, FOREIGN KEY (ticket_id) REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id)) ENGINE=InnoDB</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, name, email, phone_number, created_at) SELECT 1, 'John Doe', 'john.doe@example.com', '1234567890', '2022-01-01';</s>

CREATE TABLE tickets (ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, category VARCHAR(50), status VARCHAR(20), created_at TIMESTAMP, closed_at TIMESTAMP, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id)) ENGINE=InnoDB</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, name, email, phone_number, created_at) select 8, 'david jackson', 'david.jackson@example.com', '1239876543', '2022-01-04';</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);


CREATE TABLE tickets (
    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE agents (
    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);


CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);
</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, name, email, phone_number) SELECT 1, 'John Doe', 'john.doe@example.com', '123-456-7890';</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);

    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE agents (
    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);


CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

<t>CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);


CREATE TABLE tickets (
    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE agents (
    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE

    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),

);

    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);
</t><s>INSERT INTO tickets (ticket_id, customer_id, issue_description, status, created_at) SELECT 2, 2, 'Issue 2', 'Open', NOW();</s>

    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);


CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);


CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);
</t><s>insert into assignments (assignment_id, agent_id, ticket_id, assigned_at) select 2, 2, 2, now();</s>

    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE agents (
    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);


CREATE TABLE tickets (
    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);

    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE tickets (
    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);
</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, name, email, phone_number) select 3, 'sarah smith', 'sarah.smith@example.com', '555-123-4567';</s>

    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);


CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE tickets (
    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE agents (
    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);

    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);


CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);
</t><s>INSERT INTO agents (agent_id, name, email) SELECT 3, 'Agent Taylor', 'agent.taylor@example.com';</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE tickets (
    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);


CREATE TABLE tickets (
    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE agents (
    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);


CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);
</t><s>INSERT INTO assignments (assignment_id, agent_id, ticket_id, assigned_at) SELECT 3, 3, 3, NOW();</s>

    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);
</t><s>insert into agents (agent_id, name, email) select 4, 'agent davis', 'agent.davis@example.com';</s>

    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);


CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);
</t><s>INSERT INTO assignments (assignment_id, agent_id, ticket_id, assigned_at) SELECT 4, 4, 4, NOW();</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE assignments (
    assignment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE tickets (
    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

    agent_id INT REFERENCES agents(agent_id),
    ticket_id INT REFERENCES tickets(ticket_id),
    assigned_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);


CREATE TABLE agents (
    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);


CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);
</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, name, email, phone_number) select 5, 'emily white', 'emily.white@example.com', '444-555-6666';</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE agents (
    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);


CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);


CREATE TABLE tickets (
    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    issue_description TEXT,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Open',
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE TABLE tickets (ticket_id INT, customer_id INT, ticket_subject VARCHAR(100), ticket_description TEXT, ticket_status VARCHAR(20));

CREATE TABLE agents (agent_id INT, agent_name VARCHAR(50), agent_email VARCHAR(100), agent_phone VARCHAR(15));

CREATE TABLE departments (department_id INT, department_name VARCHAR(50));</t><s>INSERT INTO agents (agent_id, agent_name, agent_email, agent_phone) SELECT 1, 'Alice Smith', 'alice.smith@example.com', '456-789-0123'</s>

CREATE TABLE interactions (interaction_id INT, ticket_id INT, agent_id INT, interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP, interaction_text TEXT);

CREATE TABLE tickets (ticket_id INT, customer_id INT, ticket_subject VARCHAR(100), ticket_description TEXT, ticket_status VARCHAR(20));

CREATE TABLE agents (agent_id INT, agent_name VARCHAR(50), agent_email VARCHAR(100), agent_phone VARCHAR(15));</t><s>INSERT INTO agents (agent_id, agent_name, agent_email, agent_phone) SELECT 1, 'Alice Smith', 'alice.smith@example.com', '456-789-0123'</s>

CREATE TABLE tickets (ticket_id INT, customer_id INT, ticket_subject VARCHAR(100), ticket_description TEXT, ticket_status VARCHAR(20));

CREATE TABLE agents (agent_id INT, agent_name VARCHAR(50), agent_email VARCHAR(100), agent_phone VARCHAR(15));</t><s>insert into agents (agent_id, agent_name, agent_email, agent_phone) select 1, 'alice smith', 'alice.smith@example.com', '456-789-0123'</s>
